%% Diagram: Tombstone garbage collection — stability vs grace window
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Replica A
    participant B as Replica B
    participant C as Replica C
    Note over A,C: x is removed and tombstone t_x is created
    A->>A: remove x produces t_x
    A-->>B: sync t_x
    A-->>C: sync t_x (delayed)
    Note over A,C: Stability check: A waits until<br/>every replica acks t_x
    B-->>A: ack t_x
    C-->>A: ack t_x (after recovery)
    Note over A,C: Now safe to drop t_x everywhere
    A->>A: GC t_x
    B->>B: GC t_x
    C->>C: GC t_x
    Note over A,C: Time-based shortcut (Cassandra-style)<br/>drop after gc_grace_seconds<br/>RISK: a node returning after the<br/>grace window can resurrect x
